Hasil Undian Timnas indonesia U-19 Vs Myanmar 2014 AFC Cup 2014
Drawing Timnas indonesia U19 VS Myanmar U19 AFC Cup Myanmar 23 Oktober 2014
Timnas indonesia U19 vs Australia
Timnas indonesia U19 vs UEA
Timnas indonesia U19 vs Uzbekistan
indonesia u19 vs uni emirat arab u19
timnas u19 vs uae

Undian Piala Asia U-19 2014, baru saja usai. Dalam undian yang digelar di Hotel Royal Park, Yangon, Myanmar, Timnas Indonesia U-19 terhindar dari grup neraka. 
Indonesia tergabung di Grup B bersama Uzbekistan, Australia, dan Uni Emirat Arab (UEA). Dengan ini, peluang Indonesia untuk lolos ke babak perempat final cukup terbuka.
UEA sempat dilawan oleh anak-anak asuh Indra Sjafri dua kali di Tur Timur Tengah. Hasilnya, mereka mampu menang dua kali berturut-turut.
Sedangkan, Australia sedang mengalami penurunan performa. Mereka kerap menuai hasil buruk di beberapa pertandingan terakhir. Paling mencolok adalah Australia mampu dikalahkan Vietnam di babak kualifikasi Piala Asia U-19 2014, dengan skor 1-5.


Grup Neraka di Piala Asia kali ini adalah Grup C. Di sana berisi tiga negara kuat dari Asia Timur. Jepang, Korea Selatan, dan China akan bersaing untuk bisa lolos. Satu tim lainnya di Grup C adalah Vietnam.

Berikut hasil undian Piala Asia U-19 2014, Myanmar:
Grup A: Myanmar, Iran, Thailand, Yaman. 
Grup B: Uzbekistan, Australia, UEA, Indonesia. 
Grup C: Korea Selatan, Jepang, China, Vietnam.
Grup D: Irak, Korea Utara, Qatar, Oman.
title: Hasil Undian Timnas indonesia U19 AFC CUP Myanmar 2014

description: On May 4th, 2010, an American Airlines Boeing 767-200 approaching runway 22L at JFK opts to abort its approach due to high crosswind and low fuel which would make a go-around dangerous. A misunderstanding between the pilots declaring emergency and the air traffic controller is solved by the plane's crew in assertive fashion. This situation reminds me of the one Avianca 52 must have faced in 1990, also at JFK. Had Avianca's pilots been as assertive many lives might have been saved. Kudos to the American Airlines crew.
title: AA Pilot Argues with JFK Air Traffic Control

From VOA Learning English, this is the Technology Report. 
Monkeys have learned to control the movement of both arms in a computerized image of a monkey, just by thinking about moving them.  The study is part of an effort to develop brain-controlled devices for severely paralyzed patients.  Spinal cord injuries have affected millions of people worldwide.  They are unable to use or move one or more parts of the body.  The study is the work of researchers at the Duke University Center for Neuroengineering in North Carolina.  The researchers have developed what they call a brain-machine interface. It connects the brain of the monkey to a machine.  They hope it could someday be used to let someone with a spinal cord injury control an artificial arm or leg, just by thinking about it.  Early versions of the software could control only one artificial limb.  But a newer version lets rhesus monkeys move two arms at the same time as they watch a likeness of themselves on a computer screen.  Miguel Nicolelis is a neurobiology professor at Duke.  He says the monkeys first learned to control the limbs on the computer screens using joysticks.  Then the animals were trained not to move.  Professor Nicolelis says scientists are now developing a brain-controlled neuroprosthetic vest. Anyone wearing the vest would be able to move a mechanical arm or leg. The device takes electrical signals from the brain and makes them into motor commands.  These messages are then made into digital signals that a machine in the vest can understand.  Professor Nicolelis plans to show the device at the 2014 World Cup later this year.  A report on the study was published in the journal Science Translational Medicine.
title: Anh ngữ đặc biệt: Virtual Prosthetics (VOA-Tech Rep)

description: Like he did a few years ago in Porno, Homero approaches sexuality from a tangent position. Back then it was empty hours and the off-frame and the shoot of a triple X film. Now, it's the everyday life of a Spanish speaking dominatrix who lives somewhere in downtown Buenos Aires. The camera hardly ever leaves her apartment which works as both a home and a dungeon --with all the elements of her leather-metal cult-- and an anteroom from which she herself coordinates her dates. The phone is essential: through it we get to her contact with clients, her family, absent boyfriend with whom she talks about the details of their upcoming marriage. At times winy and demanding, Nadia's voice circulates through these worlds. We can hint an off-key eroticism in stories, conversations, and teases where sex is a power game, and the star of the film practices it and suffers from it. A film made of ellipsis and waiting, Sado becomes a portrait for uncertainty, and finds an unexpected comic relief in Nadia's attempts to open up to a psychologist.

Genova, (askanews) - E' drammatica la situazione maltempo in Liguria, dove le precipitazioni hanno colpito durissimamente un territorio già sofferente per le piogge torrenziali dei giorni scorsi.
La zona tra Albenga e Genova, è flagellata da precipitazioni intense che hanno determinato l'esondazione di fossi e torrenti, frane e smottamenti che stanno mettendo a rischio, l'incolumità delle persone e le attività economiche. Il capoluogo ligure è praticamente isolato.
Chiusi diversi tratti delle autostrade A10 e A7. Circolazione dei treni sospesa sulle linee da Genova a Ventimiglia, Milano e Torino per allagamenti e danneggiamenti della sede ferroviaria. Problemi anche all'aeroporto cittadino. Le autorità sconsigliano di mettersi in viaggio nell'area di Genova".
Il sindaco di Genova, Marco Doria, ha invitato la popolazione a non uscire di casa e a salire ai piani alti delle abitazioni nelle zone esondabili.
La Regione Liguria ha chiesto l'intervento dell'esercito a Genova e il potenziamento colonne mobili Protezione Civile nazionale.
title: Maltempo: situazione drammatica da Genova a Voltri

description:
This is an overview of the ESL (English as Second Language) life in Komunikasi KKI (Communication in International Class) of University of Indonesia.

[ENGLISH]
In Komunikasi KKI, students from any nationality are welcomed to join the 3.5 to 4 years of (mainly academic) journey, using two languages: their own native language and English. As KKI program is delivered in English, automatically the students will be using English as their main communication medium in class. However, they are expected to hold on to their native languages to preserve cultural and national identities.

Located in Depok, Indonesia, currently the majority of the students of Universitas Indonesia are Indonesian, thus generally their native languages are Bahasa Indonesia (Indonesian). Students can explore more of and maintain their Bahasa Indonesia in Komunikasi KKI while improving their English proficiency.

[INDONESIAN]
Program Komunikasi KKI di Universitas Indonesia menghadirkan kesempatan bagi para mahasiswanya untuk belajar dengan bahasa pengantar Inggris dan tetap bisa berbicara dan bercakap-cakap dengan santai dalam bahasa Indonesia. Dunia bilingual di Komunikasi KKI akan menjadi sangat bermanfaat untuk masa depan para mahasiswanya, karena dengan pesatnya globalisasi kini, bilingualitas dianggap menjadi suatu kualitas yang sangat bagus dan tinggi untuk seorang individu. Kalian bisa mendalami bahasa Inggris sekaligus menjaga kelestarian bahasa Indonesia kalian. Maka dari itu, mari bergabunglah dengan Komunikasi KKI Universitas Indonesia! :)

THE ROSETTA SPACE PROBE'S LONG TREK TO COMET 67P/CHURYUMOV - GERASIMENKO

What is the Difference Between Asteroids and Comets

http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/04/05/nasa-asteroid-landing_n_3023489.html

Mission to Land on a Comet

"Europe's Rosetta spacecraft is en route to intercept a comet-- and to make history. In 2014, Rosetta will enter orbit around comet 67P/Churyumov-Gerasimenkoand land a probe on it, two firsts."

European Probe on Course for a Landing on a Comet

For most students on the 40 Acres, images of 9-11 are permanent, impactful,
life altering. But for one student, the terrorist acts and aftermath created an
immediate and necessary change. For several years, the family of Wagma
Noor, had been affecting lives in their native Afghanistan. They created
education opportunities for women, while advancing awareness and visibility
of health care, nationwide. When Taliban discovered this "Westernization" of
Afghanistan, they were forced to flee their home. Wagma's goal now, is to earn
her degree in Nursing, and to finish what her parents began.

Business Details

Wine Bar and Restaurant in Morpeth Northumberland For Sale
Morpeth, Northumberland, England

Advert Ref: 3686

Business Description

Preferred Commercial is delighted to offer for sale this busy wine bar and restaurant, which was established in 1980 and which has been in our clients' careful hands since 2004. The bar is only now being offered to the market due to a change in our client's circumstances. The business trades 7 days a week and generates a turnover in the region of £154,000 per annum. Our clients offer a wide range of high quality alcohol and traditional pub food. We feel the turnover could be further increased by embarking on a modest marketing campaign to promote the business further. There is also scope to extend the opening hours and establish a website. The business has an enviable reputation and a loyal customer base, enjoying much repeat trade. The premises boast a spacious bar area and a well-equipped commercial kitchen. The property has been finished to a high standard and has been well-maintained throughout. This is an ideal opportunity to acquire an already busy bar and restaurant with scope for future growth. Early negotiations with Preferred Commercial must come highly recommended. 


Business Status

For Sale

Property

Freehold

Location


Sour Grapes occupies substantial 2-storey premises, ideally located on the main road running through Morpeth, Northumberland. The premises benefit from ample on-street parking and are situated close to a wide range of complementary businesses. The local amenities, including a school and churches are nearby. The area is well-served by public transport with numerous bus stops and a railway station within easy walking distance. The premises boast easy access to the A-road network, including the A1 and A697. Morpeth is the county town of Northumberland and is situated on the River Wansbeck. The town is surrounded by picturesque countryside and is a desirable place in which to live and work. Ashington lies 5 miles to the east, while Newcastle is 14 miles to the south.


Premises Details


Substantial 2-storey wine bar and restaurant premises. Briefly comprising:
 
 
 
Ground Floor
 
 Seating area with tables and chairs for up to 16 covers
 
 Main bar with 7 points of dispense, 4 x drink refrigerators, ice machine and electronic cash register
 
 Commercial kitchen with a range of units, 3 x refrigerators, freezer, 6-burner hob and oven, 2 x fryers, Salamander grill and sink unit
 
 Dining room with tables and chairs for up to 14 covers
 
 
 
First Floor
 
 Lounge with a range of seating and TVs
 
 
 
External
 
 Yard to rear 


Trading Hours

Mon - Thurs: 4:00pm to 11:00pm Fri - Sat: 4:00pm to 12:00am Sun: 6:00pm to 11:00pm
